issue.title: Move profiling to OpenSSL3
issue.body:
Before doing this,
- [ ] get agreement on https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/openssl/discussions/434
- [ ] do manual test runs using OSSL3 instead of OSSL111 as baseline code as per [OQS_USE_OPENSSL](https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/blob/main/CONFIGURE.md#oqs_use_openssl) and no performance deviation is visible (then also closing #74)
- [x] ensure https://github.com/openssl/openssl/pull/19968 has landed

issue.title: Investigate why x86_64 profiling values are not properly displayed
issue.body:
Since https://github.com/open-quantum-safe/profiling/pull/92 landed, classic algorithm runs results are not displayed:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/57787676/236117578-c839385e-ca3b-4ae9-858b-8dead696816c.png)

even though the values seem to be available:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/57787676/236117680-fe6c8095-916d-4e0f-81af-6067343a63a0.png)

issue.title: aarch64 and m1 testing not generating OpenSSL results
issue.body:
As exemplified by this results log excerpt: 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/57787676/236118178-50e82bd5-e8ff-4a58-8d3d-2fa7955f6375.png)

Probable reason: Use of incorrect openssl version in those architectures:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/57787676/236118381-f3b31f17-b097-4935-9b3f-7f53056aabe5.png)

issue.title: Last release fails to build after updating to gcc 13
issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
After updating gcc to version 13.1.1 I cannot build the library anymore. Main branch is okay. On top of that, I still need to manually apply the fix for sha3. It's getting difficult to maintain a package for Arch Linux. Also, note that other distros are starting to use gcc 13 as well (Fedora 38, for example).

Is there a plan for a new release?

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1. Check the versions I'm using in the logs below
2. Try to compile


**Environment (please complete the following information):**
 - OS: Archlinux
 - OpenSSL version: 3.0.8
 - Compiler version used: gcc 13.1.1
 - Build variables used:
```
build() {
    cmake -G Ninja -B build -S "${pkgname}-${pkgver}"\
        -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON \
        -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=None \
        -DCMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX="${pkgdir}/usr" \
        -DOQS_BUILD_ONLY_LIB=OFF \
        -DOQS_DIST_BUILD=ON \
        -DOQS_USE_AES_OPENSSL=ON \
        -DOQS_USE_SHA2_OPENSSL=ON \
        -DOQS_USE_SHA3_OPENSSL=ON \
        -DOQS_OPT_TARGET=x86-64 \
        -DOQS_ENABLE_SIG_RAINBOW=OFF \
        -DOQS_ENABLE_SIG_PICNIC=OFF \
        -DOQS_ENABLE_KEM_SABER=OFF \
        -DOQS_ENABLE_KEM_NTRU=OFF \
        -Wno-dev
    ninja -C build
    ninja -C build gen_docs
}
```
